title: For Sale:  GERMAN G.41 duv43 WWII NAZI 8mm Mauser Semi-Auto
location: New Jersey, New Jersey, United States
postcontent: Rather scarce WWII military rifle. This is a German G.41 semi-automatic...Hitler's answer to the M1 Garand. This rifle was manufactured in 1943 by Berlin-Lubecker Machinenfabrik (BLM) and is maker code marked "duv 43". The G.41 is a gas-operated rifle that fires the full-power 8mm Mauser cartridge. This rifle is in very good condition and has been professionally refinished/restored. The serial numbered parts are matching and there are no import markings. The magazine, barrel bands, gas cylinder and nose cone have been refinished. The buttplate has been buffed bright. There was a crack behind the receiver which has been strengthened/repaired with a bolt which has been inserted cross-wise and the ends covered with wood patches. There is a large round repair to the sling slot area and a couple of holes filled with square pegs at the underside of the butt and forend. The stock has been lightly sanded but the original cartouches are still visible on the right side of the butt. The original plastic handguard is in excellent shape without cracks. Mechanically, the rifle appears to function properly and the bore is very good, near excellent, and free of pits. A tough rifle for the collector to locate, the G.41 was produced in limited numbers as it was soon superceded by the improved G.43 semi-auto rifle. This is a very nice looking example!

title: For Trade:  Kel-Tec P 11
postcontent:
The P-11 is a semi-automatic, locked-breech, DAO, pistol, chambered for the 9mm Luger cartridge. Ten round and optional twelve round magazines available. The Kel- Tec P-11 is compact and lightweight, thanks to its locked breech. Its ergonometry, perceived recoil and practical accuracy are comparable to much larger guns. The P-11 is especially well suited for plain-clothes police officers, security personnel, or as a secondary weapon for military service members. 

TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS
Calibers: 	9 x 19 mm Luger
Weight unloaded: 	14 oz. 	400g
Loaded magazine: 	6 oz. 	159g
Length: 	5.6" 	142mm
Height: 	4.3" 	109mm
Width: 	1" 	26mm
Barrel Length: 	3.1" 	79mm
Sight radius: 	4.6" 	116mm
Muzzle Energy Max: 	400ft-lbs 	540J
Capacity: 	10 + 1
Trigger Pull: 	9 lbs 	40N

The P-11 has six main component groups: barrel, slide, frame, firing mechanism, grip, and magazine. The barrel is made of SAE 4140 Ordnance steel heat treated to 47 HRC. The slide is also 4140 steel, and contains the firing pin and the extractor. The rectangular frame is machined from solid 7075-T6 aluminum and houses the firing mechanism. The trigger connects via a transfer bar to the hammer and operates in Double Action Only. The hammer is driven by a novel free floating extension spring. The light weight firing pin transmits the energy of the hammer to ignite the primer. The functioning of the mechanism surpasses all applicable SAAMI safety standards. The grip is made of the ultra high impact polymer DuPont ST-8018. The grip also forms the magazine well and the trigger guard. Normally supplied with a 10-round double column all steel magazine.
